# Athena core — keyed run / provider selection
#
# Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in. On the Windows host, once a key is
# present the Phase 0 live smoke test un-skips (`npm test`), and provider
# switching is driven by these env vars (the SDK owns the HTTP call — see ADR 0001).

# --- Ares brain (Phase 2) — ride the live harness in place ---
# Where Athena rides the live Ares `.claude` config from. Default: OS home `.claude`
# (on Windows: C:\Users\<user>\.claude). Override to point at a different Ares home
# (e.g. the authentic-format Ares REPO in a non-Windows dev container).
# ATHENA_ARES_HOME=/home/user/Ares
#
# Under the hood buildSession({rideAres:true}) sets CLAUDE_CODE's config dir
# (CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR) to ATHENA_ARES_HOME and adds the 'user' settingSource, so the
# real Ares settings.json (its 14 py hooks, permissions, model, plugins) loads
# natively. On Windows those py hooks fire; the TS-port hooks are gated OFF then.

# --- Anthropic (Claude) — default provider ---
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.anthropic.com    # default; override below to switch provider

# --- Kimi (Moonshot) — Anthropic-compatible endpoint ---
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.moonshot.ai/anthropic
# ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=                            # Kimi key (Authorization: Bearer)
# ENABLE_TOOL_SEARCH=false                         # Kimi anthropic endpoint has no web tools
# CLAUDE_CODE_AUTO_COMPACT_WINDOW=262144           # announce Kimi context window

# --- MiniMax — Anthropic-compatible endpoint ---
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.minimax.io/anthropic
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=                               # MiniMax key (x-api-key)

# --- OpenAI — via local LiteLLM sidecar (Phase 1) ---
# The SDK points ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL at the LOCAL sidecar; the sidecar (LiteLLM)
# reads OPENAI_API_KEY and speaks the Anthropic /v1/messages shape upstream.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=                                  # real secret; consumed by the sidecar PROCESS, not the SDK
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:4000         # local sidecar (unified /v1/messages route)
# LITELLM_MASTER_KEY=                              # optional; SDK->sidecar hop auth (local, non-secret). Defaults to sk-athena-litellm-local
# ATHENA_ENABLE_SIDECAR_SPAWN=1                    # opt in to SidecarManager.start() spawning a local, pinned LiteLLM (Windows/keyed host only)
#
# Pinned LiteLLM: 1.93.0 (NEVER 1.82.7 / 1.82.8 — credential-stealing malware). See PHASE1.md.
